<br>
What do you mean by this anyway? I don't really follow. Are you saying that firing them would be a form of bigotry? Um...go look up bigotry if so.  I think firing them would be a form of &quot;you're too stupid to teach anymore, please stay away from children&quot;.  Admittedly, you probably wouldn't want to touch this issue as a 2nd grade teacher, but to actually PUNISH a child for it...um..no. Thats really really wrong.  However, I concede that they will likely get away with an apology (until I rule the world muahahahaa)<br>
<br>
I'm actually all for a &quot;reversal of the bigotry&quot; if it means that the dumb teacher involved here is forced to apologize.<br>
<br>
And, again the word gay is not derogatory when used in the context that the kid did &quot;I don't have a dad, my mommies are gay&quot;. *sigh* <br>
