<br>
Emotionally, I think they should be fired for this.  I think this display of bigotry shows very well that they're incapable of creating an environment which treats gay students as well as straight ones, and will only foster a school environment where bullying / harassment of gay students is not only tolerated, but subtly encouraged.<br>
<br>
Logically, we live in a society that affords no special rights to gays, and &quot;looks the other way&quot; when it comes to violations of rights that we all share when one of the victims is gay.  <br>
<br>
So overall, while I would certainly prefer a world where saying such a thing to a child is seen as abhorrent and justice swift, I'm realistic enough to expect little more than an apology, and even that would only come at the fear of monetary damages accompanying an ACLU student.<br>
<br>
